{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a0a716d0-ba5b-4c12-b663-a01c9d4a4c24","content":"\n\nWith **MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0**, the switch is straightforward:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Delete this line or set to false -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n   MSTest.Sdk defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform when `UseVSTest` is not set to `true`.\n\n2. **Run tests differently** — instead of `dotnet test`, you can now also use:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet run --project YourTest.csproj -- --list-tests   # list tests\n   dotnet run --project YourTest.csproj                    # run tests\n   ```\n   `dotnet test` still works but delegates to the new platform under the hood.\n\n3. **Review any VSTest-specific settings**:\n   - `.runsettings` files are still supported but some adapter-specific nodes may not apply.\n   - If you use `[DataRow]`, `[DynamicData]`, etc., those continue to work unchanged.\n   - Custom VSTest loggers (e.g., `--logger trx`) are replaced with `--report-trx` or platform-equivalent switches.\n\nThat's it — no package changes are needed since **MSTest.Sdk** already bundles the Microsoft.Testing.Platform dependencies. Just removing `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` flips the runner.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0fa704fd-33c7-4695-baf6-2d3fc3f8e6f1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing configuration, not a code change task. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":415},"id":"468d3a18-9241-4e13-a1ca-409e256e2648","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:45:37.051Z","parentId":"bbf51ff8-86da-4f27-a2bb-1e141d03f12e"}
